Ed and Paul,<br><br>
Stop bragging!<br><br>
I once had a herd of Nubian milkers! I had two ponies, I still have one. I have assorted chickens, mostly barred rocks, barn cats, and once 12 bulldogs, we bred and raised them.<br><br>
I am now down to the one pony, two goats, chickens, two barn geese, two Newfy's (150lb+ each, ask SW), a cockatoo, a sun conure, a few other birds, fish, a ginea pig, three cats, but no partridge in a pear tree, and no pear tree.<br><br>
I used to buy 600lbs rabbit chow at a clip when the immuno lab was in my garage, along with the 46 gigantic lab bunnies, and 24 exp. chickens. I have hay in my pockets, my pocket watch is 129 years old (it really is), and I am really learning to like myself!<br><br>
I have two grown up girls who love me. My wife loves me even if I AM screwed up.<br><br>
I put myself through school. I am putting my girls through school. I know I have a lot left to learn. It never stops. <br><br>
My Grandfather taught me long ago that it mattered not how much money you had, but what kind of a man you were. His truth still holds.<br><br>
Most of all, I like my BOC!<br><br>
Art<br><br>
    
